age of God – played an important role within the emergence of the codification of the Human Rights in the period of enlightenment. It is also obvious that the struggle against the politics of apartheid in South Africa was strongly supported by initiatives of churchy and other religious groups referring to the Human Rights. Christian churches and other religious groups do still play an important role in the post-apartheid South Africa. They have a public voice concerning all the challenges with which the multiethnic and economically still deeply divided South African society is faced with. The reflections on these questions in the collected lectures and essays of this volume derive from an academic discourse between German and South African scholars that took place within the German-South African Year of Science 2012/13.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aGlobalization. 0aHuman rightsxReligious aspects. 0aHuman rightszSouth Africa. 4aGlobalisierung. 4aGlobalization. 4aHuman Rights. 4aMenschenrechte. 4aSouth Africa. 4aSüdafrika. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / Anthropology.2bisacsh1 aCharbonnier, Lars, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGräb, Wilhelm, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831103847100 cprintz978311034811840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034865140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110348651423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110348651.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook